Source: Daily Southern Cross
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: His Excellency the Lieutenant-Governor proceeded to the island [Waiheke] on a Wednesday night, and left it at an early hour of the following Saturday, - the intermediate Thursday and Friday being days of a most tempestuous character - so that were his Excellency the most astucious of prospectors, he could scarcely have bestowed  a superficial glance upon a very minute superficies. - And then, with regard to those of our citizens who flew on the wings of the morning <i/>to pick up gold</i>, we imagine they were in no case to prosecute a sustained or scientific inquiry.
