Quote: Claiming to be a composer of popular songs, erstwhile member of the Fisk Jubilee Singers, one-time manager of Fullers' in Wellington, gold prospector who mushed on with the other "sourdoughs" in Alaska, oil man in California, gold prospector in New Zealand, and "professor" of music, this versatile individual might also have included in his list of accomplishments the gift of the glib tongue, and ability to talk his way into and out of anything at all.
